Somewhere along the line, sandwiches were deemed lunch food only. Yet sandwiches (better yet, panini) could not be more dinner-worthy. Case in point: these panini! Sautéed zucchini, sun-dried tomatoes, melty mozz, and creamy herb sauce are layered between ciabatta bread then pan-pressed to crispy, golden perfection. Roasted potato wedges complete the meal.

== Roasted Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning later.)

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

**Trim and discard woody bottom ends from asparagus. Swap in asparagus for potatoes; roast for 10-12 minutes. (Save potatoes for another use.)**

== Italian-Seasoned Roasted Asparagus ==

While potatoes roast, trim and cut @asparagus{6%ounce} crosswise into ¼-inch-thick
rounds. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Halve @ciabatta bread{2}. Finely chop
@sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from asparagus. Swap in asparagus for
potatoes; roast for ~{10-12%minutes}. (Save potatoes for another use.)

== Zucchini ==

Toss @zucchini{1} in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon},
half the @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. (Use the remaining Italian Seasoning as you like.)

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini
in a single layer; cook until golden brown and just tender, ~{2-4%minutes} per
side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Parsley Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon},
@sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, parsley, and remaining @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Spread a layer of creamy parsley sauce onto cut sides of ciabattas.

Fill ciabattas with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, sun-dried tomatoes, and a few
slices of zucchini. (You may have some left over—feel free to serve on the side,
if you like.)

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium heat. Once hot,
add sandwiches; press down with a #spatula{}. Cook, pressing occasionally,
until bread is toasted and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If pan seems dry when flipping sandwiches, add another drizzle of oil or
> ½ TBSP butter. Lower heat if bread browns too quickly.

Transfer panini to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, halve on a
diagonal.

Divide between #plates{} and serve with potato wedges on the side.